# Xcode (gui/) – keep project.yml + sources, drop build output and
# user-specific Xcode metadata. The .xcodeproj is regenerated from
# project.yml via `xcodegen generate` so it doesn't need to live in
# git either, but we DO commit it for now so a fresh checkout can
# `xcodebuild ... build` without needing xcodegen.
gui/build/
gui/dist/
gui/DerivedData/
gui/**/xcuserdata/
gui/**/*.xcworkspace/xcuserdata/
gui/**/.build/
gui/**/Packages/

# Locally-built daemon binary bundled into the DMG at cut time. NOT tracked
# in source -- built fresh from the ostler-assistant source repo via
# `cargo build --release --bin zeroclaw` + signed + stripped, then copied
# to assistant-agent/bin/ostler-assistant by the operator-facing
# `make ship` runner. The customer-facing GitHub release tarball is the
# durable distribution channel; this bundling is the offline-capable
# fallback that ships in DMG Resources. CX-79b (2026-05-25).
assistant-agent/bin/
# CX-88 (DMG #48g, 2026-05-29): make stage-daemon fetches the v0.4.4 daemon
# tarball from the private ostler-ai/ostler-assistant release and extracts
# the .app bundle here. Bundle phase in gui/project.yml copies it into
# OstlerInstaller.app/Contents/Resources/assistant-agent/OstlerAssistant.app/
# at xcodebuild time. NOT tracked in source -- the tarball is recreated
# on every `make ship` run.
assistant-agent/OstlerAssistant.app/
